What's a good way to write emotions for a bird?
With most others you can just assume facial control, but with a bird there's a big fucking solid mask in the way.
For example, saying "bob smiled" can convey he is happy, and "bob smiled sheepishly" can convey nervousness. With a bird there is no such option. Naturally you can use body language, but unless it is highly exaggerated, it will be hard to convey. Looks of confusion, anger, or cold analyzing can all be mistaken without the presence of a manipulatable mouth.
Without resting to colors, or dramatic bogy gestures, how does one convey that a birb is smiling with only a visual?
